!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

dirt /dɜːt/

1. N-UNCOUNT If there is dirt on something, there is dust, mud, or a stain on it. 灰尘; 污垢 

例： I started to scrub off the dirt. 我开始擦除灰尘。 

2. N-UNCOUNT You can refer to the earth on the ground as dirt , especially when it is dusty. 泥土 

例： They all sit on the dirt in the dappled shade of a tree. 他们都坐在斑驳的树荫下的地上。 

3. ADJ A dirt road or track is made from hard earth. A dirt floor is made from earth without any cement, stone, or wood laid on it. 泥土的 [ADJ n] 

例： I drove along the dirt road. 我行驶在一条土路上。 

4. N-SING If you say that you have the dirt on someone, you mean that you have information that could harm their reputation or career. 流言蜚语 [非正式] 

例： ...a sleazy reporter assigned to dig up dirt on Jack. …一名受人指使去挖掘有关杰克的流言蜚语的低级庸俗的记者。 

5. PHRASE If you say that someone treats you like dirt , you are angry with them because you think that they treat you unfairly and with no respect. 把…看得一钱不值 [表不满] 

例： People think they can treat me like dirt! 人们竟然认为可以把我完全不当一回事！

</div>

